# StationeersPlus: Developer Environment

Machine-specific paths, toolchain locations, and workflow recipes shared across every mod under this monorepo. This file is the committed scaffold. Copy it to `DEV.md` at the monorepo root (gitignored) and replace the placeholder values in angle brackets with the real paths for your machine.

Durable per-mod knowledge lives in each mod's `RESEARCH.md`; project-wide conventions live in `CLAUDE.md`.

---

## Game install

```
<STATIONEERS_INSTALL>\
  rocketstation_Data\
    Managed\                     <- game DLLs (Assembly-CSharp.dll, UnityEngine.*.dll)
    sharedassets0.assets
    resources.assets             <- prefab data (UnityPy entry point)
    ...
  BepInEx\
    core\                        <- 0Harmony.dll, BepInEx.dll
    plugins\
      StationeersLaunchPad\      <- LaunchPadBooster.dll
    config\                      <- per-mod .cfg files (BepInEx format)
    LogOutput.log                <- live log stream while game is running
```

Common defaults:

- Steam default (no custom library): `C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Stationeers\`
- Secondary Steam library: `<DRIVE>:\Steam\steamapps\common\Stationeers\` (for example `E:\Steam\steamapps\common\Stationeers\`)

`$(StationeersPath)` in `Directory.Build.props` points at this.

## BepInEx per-mod configs

Configuration files are named after the plugin GUID:

```
<STATIONEERS_INSTALL>\BepInEx\config\
  net.powertransmitterplus.cfg
  net.spraypaintplus.cfg
  net.equipmentplus.cfg
```

BepInEx preserves existing setting values across mod updates. To propagate a new default, delete the file:

```bash
rm -f "<STATIONEERS_INSTALL>/BepInEx/config/net.powertransmitterplus.cfg"
```

## Local deploy target (also the Workshop upload source)

```
<USER_DOCUMENTS>\My Games\Stationeers\
  modconfig.xml                  <- enabled local mods
  mods\
    <ModName>\                   <- deployment target, one folder per mod
      <ModName>.dll
      About\About.xml
```

Common default for Windows: `%USERPROFILE%\Documents\My Games\Stationeers\` (for example `C:\Users\<YOU>\Documents\My Games\Stationeers\`).

`modconfig.xml` is where StationeersLaunchPad knows about local (non-Workshop) mods. Each mod needs a `<Local Enabled="true"><Path Value="..." /></Local>` entry pointing at the folder above.

**This folder is the Steam Workshop upload source.** The game publishes whatever is in `mods/<ModName>/` directly to the Workshop. Every file in there ships to subscribers. Rules:

- **Always build Release** (`-p:Configuration=Release`). Never deploy a Debug build.
- **Only copy these files**: `<ModName>.dll` and the `About/` folder (`About.xml`, `Preview.png`, `thumb.png`).
- **Never copy**: `.pdb` files, `.deps.json`, `.runtimeconfig.json`, `obj/` leftovers, source files, `RESEARCH.md`, `README.md`, `TODO.md`, `LICENSE`, `NOTICE`, or any other repo file. None of those belong on the Workshop.
- **Verify before publishing**: `ls` the deploy folder and confirm it contains only the DLL and `About/`. If anything else is present, remove it before uploading.

## Steam Workshop downloads

Third-party mod installations from Workshop subscriptions:

```
<STEAM_ROOT>\steamapps\workshop\content\544550\
  <PublishedFileId>\
  ...
```

Useful for reading other mods' compiled assemblies with `ilspycmd` when patterns need confirmation.

