## Build toolchain

**MSBuild (Visual Studio)**:

```
<MSBUILD_PATH>
```

Typical locations:

- VS Community, Windows: `C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\<VERSION>\Community\MSBuild\Current\Bin\MSBuild.exe`
- VS Build Tools: `C:\Program Files (x86)\Microsoft Visual Studio\<VERSION>\BuildTools\MSBuild\Current\Bin\MSBuild.exe`

If you upgrade Visual Studio, the `<VERSION>` segment will change. No version-free alias is wired up by default.

Build a mod (adjust path and config):

```bash
"<MSBUILD_PATH>" \
  "<REPO_CLONE_PATH>/Mods/<ModName>/<ModName>.sln" \
  -t:Build -p:Configuration=Release -p:Platform="Any CPU" -v:minimal
```

Output lands in `Mods/<ModName>/<ModName>/bin/Release/<ModName>.dll`.

Deploy (Release only, Workshop-clean):

```bash
# DLL from Release build only
cp "<REPO_CLONE_PATH>/Mods/<ModName>/<ModName>/bin/Release/<ModName>.dll" \
   "<USER_DOCUMENTS>/My Games/Stationeers/mods/<ModName>/"

# About/ folder when contents changed (About.xml, Preview.png, thumb.png)
cp -r "<REPO_CLONE_PATH>/Mods/<ModName>/<ModName>/About" \
   "<USER_DOCUMENTS>/My Games/Stationeers/mods/<ModName>/"

# Verify: only DLL + About/ should be present (this folder uploads to Workshop)
ls "<USER_DOCUMENTS>/My Games/Stationeers/mods/<ModName>/"
```

StationeersLaunchPad auto-detects changed mod folders; the game must be restarted to reload patches.

