## Collaboration preferences for this developer

Project-specific / technical-depth preferences that layer on top of the global `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` settings. Customize for your own workflow.

- **Approval gate before implementation.** After research or analysis, present findings and wait for explicit confirmation before writing code. This applies even when there's a clear winner among options.
- **3 to 5 distinct solution directions on design questions**, not just one. Use comparison tables.
- **Concrete numbers and tables** over prose handwaving.
- **Clean, documented patterns** over hacky solutions, even at higher LOC cost.
- **Vanilla-look matching where possible**, deviating only when functionally justified.
- **Comprehensive test plans** with concrete steps for each change.
- **Per-mod separate config sections** (`[Visual]`, `[Pulse]`, `[Distance]`) over one big section.
- **Comfortable with technical depth**: IL details, threading semantics, decompilation, prefab extraction are all welcome.
- **Commit messages explain WHY**, not just what.

